node.text:
We're kicking off our first est film production with a momentous Malvern Home renovation by @dohertydesignstudio from est magazine issue #35.
.
Tapping into its rich architectural past and 1980s new wave bones, @dohertydesignstudio have skilfully commandeered an epic journey to reinvent this Melbourne family home. An original 1980's design by architect Peter McIntyre. .
.
Experience the entire home via the link in profile or read the full feature in est magazine issue #35. .
.
Design @dohertydesignstudio
Building design @arialexander
Builder @north_building_group 
Styling @heathernetteking 
Florals and assitant styling @rachelpolivkastylist 
Art consultant @gb.art.consulting 
Landscape design @benscott_design 
Videography @richardlipp.studio
Words @meganmayrawson
Art @tompolo @liamsnootle @anyapesce @oocaleb @davidjamesgriggs @christianthompsonartist #leekyoung-hwa 
Furniture & Objects @domoaustralia @lightlydesign @loomtowels @fenton_and_fenton @abode_living @moderntimesau @ajarfurniture @lamarzoccohomeau

node.text:
Great land. Great architecture. Great living. In an est exclusive, we feature three unique films by Rob Mills Architecture & Interiors (RMA). Australian-based RMA’s latest project, a ground-breaking residence in Byron Bay incorporates Mill’s signature use of drama, curves, lines, light and a reflection of the qualities of the land.
.
View all three films via link in profile.
.
Videography @collider__
Creative Direction | Design @robmillsarchitects

node.text:
INTERVIEW | Michael Anastassiades
​.
"Natural light can’t be replicated, but if we can understand its qualities and that experience, I believe it’s possible to try and capture it. This objective is what first attracted me to lighting."
​– Michael Anastassiades
​.
​Together with @euroluce_lighting_australia,  we caught up with @michaelanastassiades, founder of London-based design practice @studiomichaelanastassiades.
​.
​Speaking exclusively with est from his studio in North London,  Michael talks through his design evolution, process, the inspiration behind his latest collection, and long-standing partnership with @flos. Read the full feature via the link in profile. 
​.

node.text:
INTERIORS | Italian Country House
​.
​Located between the Ionian Sea and the Adriatic Sea’s coasts, this Puglia oil mill was abandoned for thirty years – until a transformation from @palombaserafini invigorated the space for modern living.
​.
​The impact of the soaring ceilings, natural materials and refined composition is a home that is perfectly geared towards rest and reflection – a home that makes it clear what the designers saw all along.
​.
​Read more about this home in the est archive – link in profile. 
​.
​Design @palombaserafini 
​Photography @francescobolisphotographer
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/italian-country-house-palombaserafini/

ARCHITECTURE | A House in Sardinia
​.
Designed by Paris-based studio @steraarchitectures, this holiday home in N​orth-east Sardinia, Italy, presents a series of volumes that appear as an extension of the rocky terrain, in colour and form. 
​.
The sculptural home fits right in in an area known for its unique architecture, stretching out to capture views of Porto Cervo through each uniquely crafted opening. 
.
​Design @steraarchitectures
Photography @matthieusalvaing, ​​Nicolas Borel & @tiziano.canu
​.

node.text:
BEST OF EST | Heritage Revivals in Melbourne’s Fitzroy
​.
​​We head to Melbourne’s Fitzroy to spotlight five heritage homes brought into the modern-day through sensitive architectural intervention.
​.
​Inside this feature you'll find this tactful revival of an early Victorian Fitzroy terrace by @robkennonarchitects.
​.
@robkennonarchitects have retained key aspects of the heritage home throughout, subtly gesturing to its 150-year-old bones through exposed original internal bluestone walls, aged Baltic Pine flooring and traditional Roman archway. 
​.
​See all four homes inside this 'Best of est' feature via the link in profile. 
​.
​Design @robkennonarchitects
​Photography @derekswalwell 
​.
​https://www.estliving.com/best-of-est-heritage-revivals-in-melbournes-fitzroy/
